  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Limited Release on 5/22/18<br/>Full Release 5 June 2018</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.1-PurchaseOrderItems-AllowDuplicates\">Purchase Order Items - Allow Duplicates</h2><p>You can now add duplicate items on a non-integrated\u00a0purchase order.\u00a0This was introduced to support ordering different variations\u00a0or grades of the same catalog item.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.1-PurchaseOrderTotals\">Purchase Order Totals</h2><p>The\u00a0purchase order add/edit screen now\u00a0calculates the order totals for you in the summary section.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.1-AccountingJournal-PurchaseOrderCosts\">Accounting Journal - Purchase Order\u00a0Costs</h2><p>The RepairQ Accounting Journal now produces entries for purchase order taxes, shipping costs, and cost adjustments.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.1-Trade-inItemInventoryNotes\">Trade-in Item Inventory Notes</h2><p>We added\u00a0an inventory item note on the trade-in item intake form, and the inventory item note will be saved\u00a0with the inventory item record. We also\u00a0added the trade-in diagnostic note field to the intake form to speed up\u00a0trade-in intake.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.1-OverheadRateonProfitabilityReport\">Overhead Rate on Profitability Report</h2><p>We are changing the calculation to be simpler to manage. Instead of applying your location overhead rate * business hours, it\u00a0will\u00a0simply become overhead rate * hours. This should make calculating an hourly overhead rate\u00a0much simpler.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.1-InvoicePrint-CustomizeTitle\">Invoice Print\u00a0- Customize Title</h2><p>Now you can customize the Invoice and Quote print titles if you wish to relabel them.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.1-ManufacturerPickListSort\">Manufacturer\u00a0Pick List Sort</h2><p>On the inventory item stock and on the trade-in intake\u00a0form the manufacturer list is now sorted alphabetically.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.15.1-CustomerCreditTransactionList\">Customer Credit Transaction List</h2><p>The transaction list was\u00a0hidden in some cases when it should have been visible. This is now fixed.</p>",
